<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-23T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-23T14:00:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.50/21: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                    Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-23T15:00:00-04:00">September 23, 1941—3
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>262. For the Under Secretary. Referring to my telegram No. 255 of
                            September 18, 5 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] p.m., Dr. Ostria Gutiérrez
                            says he would like to publish the text of his personal message to you in
                            the hope of allaying somewhat criticism to which he continues to be
                            subjected and asked if I thought you would object. I advised him to wait
                            a day or two longer in anticipation of a reply from you and promised in
                            the meantime to inquire whether or not you would consent to the
                            publication of Ostria’s message to you and your answer when it is
                            received.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>